instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kpx1719477633979.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kpx1719477633979.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kpx1719477633979.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wer1665702685657\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      &lt;x-subst type=\"inclFile\"&gt;\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">XHTML placeholder that is replaced by the contents of a specified HTML or JavaScript file.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"wer1665702685657__topic_d115799e1_d115800e1_d115801e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wer1665702685657__p_d115802e1_d115803e1_d115804e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;x-subst</code>\n            \n                              type\n                              <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"inclFile\"</code>\n            \n                              name\n                              <code class=\"ph codeph\">=\"</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"&gt;</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Content</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;/x-subst&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wer1665702685657__section_qnc_ss3_wbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d715170e86\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wer1665702685657__ul_wpx_ss3_wbc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wer1665702685657__li_d44195e1_d44196e1_d44197e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wer1665702685657__p_d115808e1_d115809e1_d115810e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>—name of the HTML or JavaScript file containing the contents\n            to be substituted.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wer1665702685657__li_d44198e1_d44199e1_d44200e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wer1665702685657__p_d115811e1_d115812e1_d115813e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Content</var>—XHTML that does not contain the\n              <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;x-subst&gt;</code> tags.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wer1665702685657__section_jqr_5s3_wbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d715170e116\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wer1665702685657__p_d115817e1_d115818e1_d115819e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">&lt;x-subst type=\"inclFile\"&gt;</span>\n        element enables external files to be included in the HTML. This can be a file containing\n        standard, reusable content, such as page headers and footers, or sections of JavaScript\n        functionality.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wer1665702685657__p_d115820e1_d115821e1_d115822e1\">You can improve the performance of very large server\n        pages by breaking them up into a number of smaller files. These are then assembled by a\n        master server page which contains only <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">&lt;x-subst&gt;</span> elements for all\n        the files to be included.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lrk1665702685508.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Substituting ProcScript Functions and Including Files in Static Server Pages</a><p>You can use the &lt;x-subst&gt; tag to substitute some ProcScript functions ($formtitle, $putmess and $text) or include files on a static server page.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gna1665702540285.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>webgen</a><p>Generate an XHTML document from the layout definition and the component definition of a static server page.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7421842\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7421842\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "<x-subst type=\"inclFile\"> Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 27, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 <x-subst type=\"inclFile\"> XHTML placeholder that is replaced by the contents of a specified HTML or JavaScript file. <x-subst type = \"inclFile\" name =\" FileName \"> Content </x-subst> Arguments FileName —name of the HTML or JavaScript file containing the contents to be substituted. Content —XHTML that does not contain the <x-subst> tags. Description The <x-subst type=\"inclFile\"> element enables external files to be included in the HTML. This can be a file containing standard, reusable content, such as page headers and footers, or sections of JavaScript functionality. You can improve the performance of very large server pages by breaking them up into a number of smaller files. These are then assembled by a master server page which contains only <x-subst> elements for all the files to be included. Related Links Substituting ProcScript Functions and Including Files in Static Server Pages You can use the <x-subst> tag to substitute some ProcScript functions ($formtitle, $putmess and $text) or include files on a static server page. webgen Generate an XHTML document from the layout definition and the component definition of a static server page. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}